Ok. Bye

832
01:16:14,782 --> 01:16:16,443
Bhairav Singh

833
01:16:17,852 --> 01:16:19,342
l am coming to get you...

834
01:16:21,722 --> 01:16:23,781
Do you understand recession?

835
01:16:24,325 --> 01:16:25,792
Disgraceful.

836
01:16:56,290 --> 01:16:57,484
Was this picnic your idea?

837
01:16:58,826 --> 01:17:01,351
Your father isn't as bad
as you make him out to be.

838
01:17:02,230 --> 01:17:06,064
l just don't get him.
Sometimes a demon, sometimes a lamb.

839
01:17:07,835 --> 01:17:10,030
Spoken like a true writer...

840
01:17:11,105 --> 01:17:12,367
l'm not talking like a writer...

841
01:17:13,107 --> 01:17:16,440
Your mother would have been
proud if she were alive today.

842
01:17:16,978 --> 01:17:18,843
She always wanted you
to be a writer.

843
01:17:19,180 --> 01:17:20,374
Really?
- Yes.

844
01:17:21,449 --> 01:17:24,907
She never told your
father but she told me...

845
01:17:25,853 --> 01:17:30,790
How she would've loved that line...
Sometimes a demon, sometimes a lamb.

846
01:17:33,461 --> 01:17:38,125
Sometimes a demon,
sometimes a lamb.

847
01:17:38,199 --> 01:17:40,861
Stop it!

848
01:17:50,011 --> 01:17:53,412
l have an idea...

849
01:17:53,481 --> 01:17:55,472
What is it?

850
01:17:57,985 --> 01:17:59,316
Let's hear one of Rohan's poems...

851
01:18:04,158 --> 01:18:06,023
He's written a full-length novel...

852
01:18:07,495 --> 01:18:10,555
l'm not asking you to
change your mind ...

853
01:18:11,165 --> 01:18:14,498
Listen to it. lf you
don't like it, don't applaud.

854
01:18:18,039 --> 01:18:20,166
Come on big man, go for it.

855
01:18:24,512 --> 01:18:29,506
lf you could see past the shore,
You would know what l think.

856
01:18:30,451 --> 01:18:35,184
lf you could hear the waves,
You would know what l think.

857
01:18:36,324 --> 01:18:41,125
Remove your veil of obstinacy,
And look beyond the window.

858
01:18:42,063 --> 01:18:46,591
lf you could see through convention,
You would know what l think.

859
01:18:47,868 --> 01:18:52,896
lf you had faith in yourself as l do,
You could walk with me a while...

860
01:18:53,941 --> 01:18:58,435
lf you could see the colors l do,
You could walk with me a while.

861
01:18:59,480 --> 01:19:01,880
lf you want to touch the sky as l do,

862
01:19:01,949 --> 01:19:04,179
Then your desires would come alive.

863
01:19:04,952 --> 01:19:09,616
Then, in my next life, we
could fly together a while.

864
01:19:17,431 --> 01:19:18,489
Forget it

865
01:19:19,500 --> 01:19:20,899
A woman's magazine will publish it...

866
01:19:20,968 --> 01:19:23,266
...or someone will drop a
coin in your begging bowl.

867
01:20:11,886 --> 01:20:12,944
Hello.

868
01:20:15,990 --> 01:20:17,048
Please... sit...

869
01:20:17,691 --> 01:20:18,749
Hello

870
01:20:18,826 --> 01:20:19,884
How are you?
- Please, have a seat.

871
01:20:19,960 --> 01:20:21,018
How was the journey?

872
01:20:21,362 --> 01:20:23,330
Okay. Our flight got a bit delayed.

873
01:20:24,899 --> 01:20:26,423
l made these for you to read.

874
01:20:50,391 --> 01:20:55,124
They're good...

875
01:20:56,330 --> 01:20:58,025
l'm glad you came today.

876
01:20:59,066 --> 01:21:00,397
l'm off to Kolkata tomorrow...

877
01:21:00,868 --> 01:21:03,462
Let me show you the workshop.

878
01:21:04,271 --> 01:21:05,329
Sure.

879
01:21:10,878 --> 01:21:11,936
Hello?

880
01:21:12,012 --> 01:21:13,479
ls that Mr. Singh?
- Yes?

881
01:21:13,814 --> 01:21:17,181
l'm Mrs Batra here,
Principal of Arjun's school.

882
01:21:17,251 --> 01:21:18,809
Yes Mrs Batra, tell me.

883
01:21:18,886 --> 01:21:22,014
There's been another problem with
your son, Arjun, this morning...

884
01:21:22,823 --> 01:21:25,792
We'd like you to come here
and take him back home today.

885
01:21:27,027 --> 01:21:30,019
l'm in a meeting right now.
Can l come post lunch?

886
01:21:30,297 --> 01:21:33,095
No Mr. Singh. This is an
extremely serious problem.

887
01:21:33,167 --> 01:21:34,259
l know Mrs. Batra but...

888
01:21:35,369 --> 01:21:37,132
Keep him in your office for sometime.

889
01:21:37,204 --> 01:21:38,762
Mr. Singh please understand

890
01:21:38,839 --> 01:21:41,103
l cannot allow Arjun to
remain in school today.

891
01:21:42,109 --> 01:21:44,373
Okay, l'm coming.

892
01:21:44,445 --> 01:21:45,503
ln half an hour?

893
01:21:45,579 --> 01:21:46,910
Yes Mrs. Batra. l'm coming right now.

894
01:21:46,981 --> 01:21:48,039
Thank you, Mr. Singh.

895
01:21:51,385 --> 01:21:55,515
l'm sorry, but l have to
rush to my son's school.

896
01:21:55,856 --> 01:21:59,189
He's been unwell
recently and it got worse today.

897
01:21:59,260 --> 01:22:03,128
But Mr. Rao will show
you around the workshop.

898
01:22:03,197 --> 01:22:05,859
No problem. We'll come back tomorrow.

899
01:22:05,933 --> 01:22:08,197
We have other factories to see today.

900
01:22:08,335 --> 01:22:12,032
But l told you, l have to be in
Kolkata tomorrow. l've committed it.

901
01:22:12,473 --> 01:22:14,532
l am sorry. We can't stay any longer.

902
01:22:15,409 --> 01:22:18,435
Anyway. We'll meet again.
Some other time?

903
01:22:19,146 --> 01:22:20,204
Okay...

904
01:22:20,414 --> 01:22:21,472
Let's go.

905
01:22:51,912 --> 01:22:52,970
What happened?

906
01:22:53,180 --> 01:22:54,238
Get in the car.

907
01:23:13,400 --> 01:23:14,458
What happened?

908
01:23:15,869 --> 01:23:17,029
His blood pressure is very low.

909
01:23:17,538 --> 01:23:19,438
Seems like he's had a bad fall.

910
01:23:20,207 --> 01:23:21,504
There could be internal bleeding.

911
01:23:22,343 --> 01:23:25,244
l'll have to check. We'll keep him
under observation for a few days.

912
01:23:25,312 --> 01:23:26,370
How many days?

913
01:23:26,947 --> 01:23:28,005
Four to five days.

914
01:23:28,082 --> 01:23:29,140
Four to five days?

915
01:23:29,216 --> 01:23:32,242
Don't worry. He'll
be fine. Don't worry.

916
01:23:33,153 --> 01:23:34,211
Thank you.

917
01:23:37,891 --> 01:23:38,949
How did it happen?

918
01:23:39,493 --> 01:23:40,551
Fell down the stairs.

919
01:23:41,962 --> 01:23:43,020
How?

920
01:23:43,430 --> 01:23:45,955
How should l know? He just fell.

921
01:23:50,237 --> 01:23:51,636
You go home. l'll stay here.

922
01:23:52,973 --> 01:23:54,031
l'm also staying.

923
01:23:58,579 --> 01:23:59,637
What happened to your results?

924
01:24:00,914 --> 01:24:02,643
l passed.
- Marks?

925
01:24:03,984 --> 01:24:06,043
They're good.
- Good.

926
01:24:14,528 --> 01:24:16,120
l'm going to Kolkata for three days.

927
01:24:18,265 --> 01:24:21,166
lf all goes well, l'll
return with a few contracts.

928
01:24:22,269 --> 01:24:24,169
You stay here with Arjun.

929
01:24:24,471 --> 01:24:26,996
And don't leave him alone, okay?

930
01:24:27,074 --> 01:24:28,132
Yes Sir.

931
01:24:33,480 --> 01:24:34,538
And...

932
01:24:35,082 --> 01:24:37,141
No need to inform Uncle and Auntie.

933
01:24:38,285 --> 01:24:41,686
l've told them that both of
you are going with me. Okay?

934
01:24:42,022 --> 01:24:43,080
Yes Sir.

935
01:24:45,426 --> 01:24:46,484
Fine.

936
01:24:56,303 --> 01:24:57,361
Have you eaten?

937
01:25:04,645 --> 01:25:06,044
Sir has gone to kolkata.

938
01:25:08,582 --> 01:25:09,640
Aren't you happy?

939
01:25:18,192 --> 01:25:19,250
What happened yesterday?

940
01:25:48,288 --> 01:25:49,346
For you.

941
01:25:57,030 --> 01:25:58,088
And these...

942
01:25:58,165 --> 01:25:59,757
lf you feel like reading.

943
01:26:08,242 --> 01:26:10,642
This has my poems and stories.

944
01:26:11,311 --> 01:26:12,369
Would you like to hear some?

945
01:26:16,650 --> 01:26:17,708
Hello Arjun.

946
01:26:19,453 --> 01:26:20,579
Are you feeling well today?

947
01:26:21,288 --> 01:26:22,346
Good.

948
01:26:28,328 --> 01:26:29,590
Could you change his clothes?

949
01:26:29,663 --> 01:26:31,130
Yes.
- Thank you.

950
01:26:35,669 --> 01:26:36,727
What is it?

951
01:27:06,099 --> 01:27:07,157
What now?

952
01:28:06,159 --> 01:28:11,153
Lunch was to be served by 12.30.
lts 1 :00 p.m now.

953
01:28:11,231 --> 01:28:13,165
Please don't shout. lt's bad for you.

954
01:28:13,233 --> 01:28:14,461
Yes l know.

955
01:28:14,768 --> 01:28:16,167
l can get a heart attack.

956
01:28:16,236 --> 01:28:18,329
But if l die of hunger before that?

957
01:28:18,405 --> 01:28:20,464
l'll go and get your food just now.

958
01:28:20,908 --> 01:28:22,170
Get it fast...

959
01:28:22,709 --> 01:28:24,904
Corpses don't eat.

960
01:28:29,783 --> 01:28:30,909
Why don't you laugh?

961
01:28:32,386 --> 01:28:33,512
l am 80 years old...

962
01:28:34,521 --> 01:28:35,920
Grandfather of six.

963
01:28:36,423 --> 01:28:37,720
Great grandfather of two...

964
01:28:38,191 --> 01:28:39,249
Can't l shout?

965
01:28:40,193 --> 01:28:41,251
Laugh.

966
01:28:42,195 --> 01:28:43,253
Laugh.

967
01:28:58,645 --> 01:28:59,703
Would you like to listen to a poem?

968
01:29:10,824 --> 01:29:11,882
Chandu's Cycle.

969
01:29:12,759 --> 01:29:15,227
Chandu's cycle was
just like Chandu...

970
01:29:15,829 --> 01:29:18,696
As it moved, it crickered and
crankered, just like Chandu.

971
01:29:19,566 --> 01:29:22,626
The handle was as light
as Chandu's slender hand.

972
01:29:23,236 --> 01:29:26,262
The pedals were as thin
as Chandu's spindle legs.

973
01:29:27,240 --> 01:29:30,232
The seat was as broad
as Chandu's huge behind.

974
01:29:30,978 --> 01:29:34,243
The carrier was as small
as Chandu's short career.

975
01:29:34,781 --> 01:29:36,373
Yet it was Chandu's true friend.

976
01:29:36,850 --> 01:29:38,283
Was always loyal to Chandu.

977
01:29:39,252 --> 01:29:42,779
lt took Chandu's
heavy weight with ease.

978
01:29:43,357 --> 01:29:46,793
One day the cycle broke down.

979
01:29:47,260 --> 01:29:49,251
Seeing a bull charging at him,

980
01:29:49,363 --> 01:29:50,694
Chandu dropped it hard.

981
01:29:51,264 --> 01:29:54,256
When Monty Mechanic
could not save the cycle,

982
01:29:54,935 --> 01:29:58,268
Chandu's father sold
it to a scrap dealer.

983
01:29:58,739 --> 01:30:02,266
Chandu drowned himself in his books.

984
01:30:02,409 --> 01:30:05,378
Like he had an old dream to fulfill.

985
01:30:06,013 --> 01:30:07,412
Later, when Chandu grew up,

986
01:30:07,814 --> 01:30:09,281
He used his very first salary...

987
01:30:09,683 --> 01:30:13,278
And got himself a new cycle...

988
01:30:14,287 --> 01:30:15,345
But...

989
01:30:15,522 --> 01:30:16,580
But?

990
01:30:16,823 --> 01:30:20,281
This cycle too was
just like Chandu...

991
01:30:20,627 --> 01:30:23,289
lt still crickered and
crankered as it moved around.

992
01:30:23,830 --> 01:30:25,297
lt's seat was...

993
01:30:25,365 --> 01:30:27,424
As broad as Chandu's huge behind.

994
01:30:27,634 --> 01:30:29,295
The carrier was as small...

995
01:30:29,369 --> 01:30:31,303
As Chandu's short career.

996
01:30:34,307 --> 01:30:35,365
You wrote that?

997
01:30:36,543 --> 01:30:38,306
Yes
- Wow...

998
01:30:38,979 --> 01:30:40,037
Very good.

999
01:30:40,914 --> 01:30:42,313
Very inspiring !

1000
01:30:42,549 --> 01:30:44,983
Thank you.
- Keep writing like this, son.

1001
01:30:45,719 --> 01:30:47,050
Keep writing.

1002
01:30:48,388 --> 01:30:50,982
Write.

1003
01:30:59,933 --> 01:31:02,925
How many friends do
you have in school?

1004
01:31:06,339 --> 01:31:07,397
Seven.

1005
01:31:07,474 --> 01:31:08,532
Their names?

1006
01:31:08,742 --> 01:31:09,800
Apurva,

1007
01:31:10,343 --> 01:31:11,742
Sunny, Raju,

1008
01:31:11,812 --> 01:31:13,336
Batuk, Kunal...

1009
01:31:13,580 --> 01:31:15,514
Kunal...Kunal,

1010
01:31:15,582 --> 01:31:16,640
Veer.

1011
01:31:17,350 --> 01:31:18,408
And?

1012
01:31:18,618 --> 01:31:19,676
And...

1013
01:31:20,887 --> 01:31:21,945
That's only six.

1014
01:31:24,357 --> 01:31:25,551
And one more...

1015
01:31:26,827 --> 01:31:27,885
Tushar.

1016
01:31:28,361 --> 01:31:29,692
You have so many friends.

1017
01:31:30,363 --> 01:31:31,557
l have only three.

1018
01:31:32,899 --> 01:31:34,423
What was your mother like?

1019
01:31:35,368 --> 01:31:37,734
My mother was very nice.

1020
01:31:38,972 --> 01:31:40,439
She loved me a lot.

1021
01:31:41,374 --> 01:31:42,602
She smelled wonderful

1022
01:31:42,676 --> 01:31:44,371
when l'd cuddle up to sleep.

1023
01:31:45,045 --> 01:31:46,376
Just like a mother.

1024
01:31:48,482 --> 01:31:50,450
l don't know what
my mother was like.

1025
01:31:51,051 --> 01:31:52,382
Do you know her?

1026
01:31:53,987 --> 01:31:55,045
No.

1027
01:32:02,729 --> 01:32:03,787
Mr Poet...

1028
01:32:06,399 --> 01:32:07,627
Why don't you ever laugh?

1029
01:32:09,002 --> 01:32:10,060
Yes.

1030
01:32:10,137 --> 01:32:12,401
Look at you now. You look so good.

1031
01:32:14,007 --> 01:32:15,406
When do we hear something new?

1032
01:32:15,709 --> 01:32:16,767
Tonight?

1033
01:32:16,943 --> 01:32:18,001
ln the night?

1034
01:32:18,745 --> 01:32:20,007
Do you also write at night?

1035
01:32:20,413 --> 01:32:21,471
Sometimes.

1036
01:32:21,548 --> 01:32:22,674
Beware of the night ...

1037
01:32:23,483 --> 01:32:24,541
You see ...

1038
01:32:24,885 --> 01:32:26,409
The day destroys the night,

1039
01:32:26,753 --> 01:32:28,015
Night divides the day.

1040
01:32:28,588 --> 01:32:29,646
Try to run,

1041
01:32:29,956 --> 01:32:31,014
Try to hide...

1042
01:32:31,158 --> 01:32:32,557
Break on through to the other side.

1043
01:32:35,495 --> 01:32:38,430
This is the true
story of three friends...

1044
01:32:38,698 --> 01:32:41,428
Muninder, Benoy and Rohit.

1045
01:32:41,802 --> 01:32:45,431
The kingdom where
they lived would select

1046
01:32:45,505 --> 01:32:47,439
the smartest boys for training.

1047
01:32:47,774 --> 01:32:52,040
Years later, they would join
the King's prestigious army.

1048
01:32:52,712 --> 01:32:56,443
But nobody really knew what
went on inside the castle.

1049
01:32:56,983 --> 01:33:00,441
Their parents didn't know
that the King's evil minister,

1050
01:33:00,520 --> 01:33:03,887
Was brain-washing the kids
and turning them into robots.

1051
01:33:04,191 --> 01:33:05,453
ls it a true story?

1052
01:33:05,525 --> 01:33:06,583
Yes.

1053
01:33:06,660 --> 01:33:09,458
The wicked man's name was Rathod.

1054
01:33:09,529 --> 01:33:10,587
Rathod!

1055
01:33:10,664 --> 01:33:11,858
Yes, Rathod.

1056
01:34:16,062 --> 01:34:18,155
Vikreet and Benoy were
with the full Robot Army...

1057
01:34:18,531 --> 01:34:20,522
Muninder and the kids
were due any minute now...

1058
01:34:20,834 --> 01:34:23,826
Rohit was worried.
They hadn't come yet.

1059
01:34:24,271 --> 01:34:28,537
He turned around. And froze.
A terrified look came into his eyes.

1060
01:34:29,209 --> 01:34:31,200
He saw someone
coming through the tunnel.

1061
01:34:31,878 --> 01:34:33,675
Someone was coming from the tunnel...

1062
01:34:33,747 --> 01:34:34,873
Who was coming?

1063
01:34:38,785 --> 01:34:40,218
Who was it?

1064
01:34:46,159 --> 01:34:48,184
We'll finish tomorrow...
- Now!

1065
01:34:54,901 --> 01:34:56,027
34 in Chemistry

1066
01:34:57,570 --> 01:34:59,697
20 in Physics. 15 in Maths.

1067
01:35:01,041 --> 01:35:02,565
You told me you passed.

1068
01:35:04,177 --> 01:35:08,238
ls this a joke to you?

1069
01:35:09,649 --> 01:35:12,584
l thought you'd finally
become serious about your studies.

1070
01:35:12,652 --> 01:35:17,112
You're narrating
stories to half-dead people.

1071
01:35:17,190 --> 01:35:18,589
Just to hear them tell you
what a good writer you are.

1072
01:35:20,593 --> 01:35:21,651
What are you staring at?

1073
01:35:22,595 --> 01:35:23,653
Lower your eyes.

1074
01:35:24,998 --> 01:35:27,262
lf this wasn't a hospital,
l would skin you right now.

1075
01:35:28,601 --> 01:35:31,593
l'm not going to
forget this in a hurry.

1076
01:35:32,906 --> 01:35:36,842
Come home. l'll make
sure l get an answer.

1077
01:35:44,284 --> 01:35:45,615
What did Sir say?

1078
01:35:45,752 --> 01:35:48,619
Sir said that he will send
me to the hospital as well.

1079
01:35:48,755 --> 01:35:49,813
Why?

1080
01:35:50,690 --> 01:35:51,816
Because l failed my exams.

1081
01:35:53,326 --> 01:35:55,624
So you'll go back to
boarding school?

1082
01:35:56,162 --> 01:35:57,220
No. Why?

1083
01:35:57,297 --> 01:36:01,927
Sir said if l don't pass,
he'll send me to a boarding school.

1084
01:37:19,712 --> 01:37:21,043
What happened that day?

1085
01:37:22,382 --> 01:37:23,713
Sir hit me.

1086
01:37:25,718 --> 01:37:26,776
Why?

1087
01:37:26,853 --> 01:37:31,313
Two boys were teasing me at school.
l broke one's teeth.

1088
01:37:33,726 --> 01:37:34,784
Did he beat you a lot?

1089
01:37:34,861 --> 01:37:36,726
He beat me with a belt.

1090
01:38:32,252 --> 01:38:33,310
Shall we go?

1091
01:38:48,468 --> 01:38:49,799
How old are you?

1092
01:38:57,977 --> 01:38:59,501
l'm asking you something.

1093
01:39:00,413 --> 01:39:01,471
How old are you?

1094
01:39:03,816 --> 01:39:04,874
Seventeen.

1095
01:39:05,818 --> 01:39:06,876
Seventeen...

